# Command Center - your keys
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your own key(s). .env is gitignored, so it
# never reaches GitHub - the same habit from Project 01.

# Anthropic - for the Command Console and Intel Feed (the AI modules).
# Get yours at https://console.anthropic.com (API keys). Add a little credit
# under Billing; each AI call costs pennies. This is the same key from Projects
# 01 and 10.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=

# Alpha Vantage - OPTIONAL, only if you want stock prices (e.g. AAPL, NVDA)
# alongside your crypto. Free key at https://www.alphavantage.co/support/#api-key
# (5 calls/min, so refresh stocks gently). Leave blank to track crypto only.
ALPHA_VANTAGE_KEY=

# Crypto (BTC, SOL) uses CoinGecko's free public API - NO key needed, exactly
# like Project 04.

# HOW THE KEY GETS USED (your agent handles the details - see README rule 4):
#  - Recommended: a small serverless function (Project 01 pattern, run with
#    `netlify dev`) reads ANTHROPIC_API_KEY here on the SERVER and calls Anthropic
#    for you - the key never reaches the browser. Keep the name as-is.
#  - Shortcut, local only: if you call Anthropic straight from browser code built
#    with Vite, only names starting with VITE_ are readable there
#    (e.g. VITE_ANTHROPIC_API_KEY) - and that key is then PUBLIC, so local use only.
# Either way the key lives in .env (gitignored), never in committed code.
